A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Election Law – Voter Registration List – Absentee Voters
3 (Absentee Ballot Transparency Act of 2025)
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the State Board of Elections or a local board of elections, on
5 request of a candidate, to provide the candidate with a list of registered voters who
6 have requested an absentee ballot for an upcoming election; requiring that the list
7 of absentee voters provided include certain contact information for each voter; and
8 generally relating to lists of absentee voters.
9 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
10 Article – Election Law
11 Section 3–506(a)
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – Election Law
17 3–506.
18 (a) (1) A copy of a list of registered voters shall be provided to a Maryland
19 registered voter on receipt of:
20 (i) a written application; and
21 (ii) a statement, signed under oath, that the list is not intended to be
22 used for:
