1 1. commercial solicitation; or
2 2. any other purpose not related to the electoral process.
3 (2) In consultation with the local boards, the State Board shall adopt
4 regulations that specify:
5 (i) the time for a list to be provided under this subsection;
6 (ii) the authorization to be required for providing a list;
7 (iii) the fee to be paid for providing a list;
8 (iv) the information to be included on a list;
9 (v) that the residence address of an individual who is a participant
10 in an address confidentiality program may not be disclosed;
11 (vi) that a participant in an address confidentiality program is not
12 required to apply to the State Board to keep the individual’s residence address confidential;
13 (vii) the format of the information; and
14 (viii) the medium or media on which the information is to be provided.
15 (3) (I) IN ACCORDANCE WITH PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS
16 SUBSECTION AND REGULATIONS ADOPTED UNDER PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS
17 SUBSECTION, ON REQUEST OF A CANDIDATE, THE STATE BOARD OR A LOCAL BOARD
18 SHALL PROVIDE THE CANDIDATE WITH A LIST OF REGISTERED VOTERS WHO HAVE
19 REQUESTED AN ABSENTEE BALLOT FOR AN UPCOMING ELECTION.
20 (II) A LIST OF REGISTERED VOTERS PROVIDED TO A CANDIDATE
21 UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF THIS PARAGRAPH SHALL INCLUDE THE E–MAIL
22 ADDRESS AND TELEPHONE NUMBER OF EACH VOTER ON THE LIST IF THE
23 INFORMATION IS AVAILABLE.
24 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
25 October 1, 2025.

